1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:02,167
<i>Tell me what Dad did
so that I'll know,</i>

2
00:00:02,167 --> 00:00:04,000
<i>I could correct it and stop
you guys from being mad at me.</i>

3
00:00:04,133 --> 00:00:06,367
Edward, he has other intentions
<i> on the hotel.</i>

4
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:08,800
<i>He wants to take
the hidden treasure.</i>

5
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:09,967
<i> Treasure?</i>

6
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,033
<i> Andy can't do this alone.</i>

7
00:00:11,167 --> 00:00:12,967
<i>He's getting help from someone
with power.</i>

8
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:14,500
<i> We have evidence.</i>

9
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,533
<i>It's undeniable
that this is De La Paz.</i>

10
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:19,333
<i>This isn't enough evidence
for me to investigate her.</i>

11
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:21,333
<i>We're putting ourselves
in danger.</i>

12
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:23,933
As long as Andy's roaming free,
<i> we're all in danger.</i>

13
00:00:24,067 --> 00:00:26,833
<i>And most importantly,
I'll remind all of you,</i>

14
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:30,100
<i>this is for our father's
unjust deaths</i>

15
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,933
<i>just because of that damn
treasure.</i>

16
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:34,300
<i>It's clear to Andy
that there are clues.</i>

17
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:36,200
<i>He'll have someone tail us
for sure.</i>

18
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:37,600
<i> We'll have each other's backs.</i>

19
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,367
We only have each other anyway.

20
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:40,633
<i> Change of plans.</i>

21
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,633
<i>For now we'll follow
Michael's kids</i>

22
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:44,233
<i>in their search
for the treasure</i>

23
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:45,533
<i>then we'll get it
when they find it.</i>

24
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,133
<i> Take care, alright?</i>

25
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:49,467
<i>You and Martin
do the same, please.</i>

26
00:00:54,767 --> 00:01:01,767
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]
- [CICADAS BUZZING]

27
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:06,167
Are you sure this is the way
to, what was it, the shrine?

28
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,767
I checked with Sari.

29
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,667
It's not far up the peak
of the mountain

30
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:12,167
so I think we won't have
any trouble getting there.

31
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:15,733
[LEAVES CRUNCHING]

32
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:16,767
Shh.

33
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:18,000
Why?

34
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:24,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:01:26,667 --> 00:01:27,900
[WHISPERING] Someone's here...

36
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:29,800
Is this it?

37
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:31,767
Are we being followed
by Andy's--

38
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:40,367
[LEAVES CRUNCHING]

39
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:49,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:58,833
[LEAVES CRUNCHING]

41
00:02:01,633 --> 00:02:04,367
[LEAVES CRUNCHING]

42
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:09,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CRESCENDOS]

43
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:16,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

44
00:03:09,267 --> 00:03:16,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

45
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:38,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

46
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:45,833
[SCREAMS]

47
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,133
I knew it.

48
00:03:48,267 --> 00:03:49,633
Why did you follow us here?

49
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:52,733
- Si-- Sir, I just want to help.
- [SIGHS]

50
00:03:52,867 --> 00:03:54,700
I already have Justin here!

51
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:57,300
But,

52
00:03:57,433 --> 00:04:00,267
he doesn't look like
he's made it to the shrine, sir!

53
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,300
Actually, yeah I haven't.

54
00:04:02,433 --> 00:04:03,667
See?

55
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:06,967
I've been there before
so I can lead the way!

56
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:08,233
No, Sari.

57
00:04:08,633 --> 00:04:10,400
We'll figure it out
just go home!

58
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:12,133
If Sari's been there before,

59
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,167
then we could get there faster.

60
00:04:14,767 --> 00:04:15,867
We could find the clue faster.

61
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:20,100
And we could head home earlier!
That's it, Sir Justin!

62
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:21,767
You could get in danger.

63
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:24,133
Sir, I grew up
in the countryside.

64
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:25,967
I won't be in danger!

65
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:27,233
And if she does,

66
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,333
I'll take responsibility
for Sari.

67
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:31,200
Way to gang up on me.

68
00:04:31,867 --> 00:04:33,367
[JUSTIN] I'm just being
practical.

69
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:34,500
What do you say, Sari?

70
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,867
Lead the way!

71
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,067
Let's go!

72
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,800
Follow me, good sirs!

73
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:42,433
[MARTIN SIGHS]

74
00:04:42,567 --> 00:04:49,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

75
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,433
"Follow the path silently.

76
00:04:59,567 --> 00:05:01,933
The secret lies not in script

77
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:04,800
but on the back
sculpted by time.

78
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:07,400
Peruse the lines
as if it were a vow

79
00:05:07,533 --> 00:05:10,300
for this is where
the Oscalara sighs."

80
00:05:11,433 --> 00:05:12,933
[EXHALING HEAVILY]

81
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:15,067
We've read it
for so many times now

82
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,933
but we still couldn't
figure out where it is.

83
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:19,267
Maybe the book mentions
something else.

84
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:25,333
[BOOK PAGES RUSTLING]

85
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:26,667
Jade.

86
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:31,100
What are you doing here?

87
00:05:32,567 --> 00:05:34,167
I'll help you.

88
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,900
With what?

89
00:05:37,067 --> 00:05:38,600
In searching for the treasure.

90
00:05:38,733 --> 00:05:42,500
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:45,067
Treasure? What are you
talking about?

92
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:49,333
[EDWARD] I know you're looking
for Hotel 88's treasure.

93
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:52,900
Jade.

94
00:05:58,433 --> 00:05:59,900
I told him about it.

95
00:06:00,033 --> 00:06:02,267
Jade, why did you do that?

96
00:06:08,567 --> 00:06:09,533
Come with me.

97
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:16,767
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:20,267
- [SIGHS]
- [BAG RUSTLES]

99
00:06:25,033 --> 00:06:26,767
Why did you spill it to him?

100
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:29,867
- Kiko, it's Uncle Andy who's--
- Jade.

101
00:06:30,467 --> 00:06:31,633
He's the son of the enemy

102
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,367
of course he'll side
with his father!

103
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,700
Don't you get that?!

104
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,533
He's not doing anything wrong!

105
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:38,533
Really? You sure about that?

106
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:41,133
Why? Are you monitoring him
for 24 hours

107
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,600
to know that he doesn't?

108
00:06:43,433 --> 00:06:46,267
Maybe Andy didn't say anything
when we talked to him

109
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,900
because he already
ratted us out to his father.

110
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:52,000
Out of all of us,
I know Edward the best.

111
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:57,400
Believe it or not,
I didn't tell Dad anything.

112
00:06:57,533 --> 00:07:00,167
Just like all of you, I just
want to know the truth.

113
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:02,300
Or are you interested
in the treasure too?

114
00:07:02,433 --> 00:07:03,800
I'm already rich.

115
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:05,200
I don't need any more.

116
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:07,733
Oh but your father is rich too
and is still greedy for more.

117
00:07:07,867 --> 00:07:09,767
There's nothing I want most
right now

118
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,000
but to know the truth.

119
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,300
If what you're saying
about Dad is true,

120
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,333
then I can protect you
if I'm there.

121
00:07:19,467 --> 00:07:22,333
- Aren't you confident--
- 'Cause it's the truth, Kiko.

122
00:07:23,233 --> 00:07:25,433
He won't lay a finger on any
of you if you're with me.

123
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:31,467
Kiko, please.

124
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:34,200
Edward grew up
on this island too.

125
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,200
Maybe he can help us
on our search.

126
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,900
Alright. Fine.

127
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:42,767
Since you already know a lot,

128
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:45,433
I'll let you join.

129
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:48,300
Not because I trust you

130
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:50,767
or because of this hero act
you're putting on.

131
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:53,767
I'll be keeping this.

132
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:02,167
Jade.

133
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:04,733
Thank you.

134
00:08:05,933 --> 00:08:08,233
I hope you don't break my trust.

135
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:11,833
Because not only
am I clashing with Kiko,

136
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:14,967
but his and my own family
as well.

137
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:22,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

138
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,933
[LUNA] This seems different
from the first place we went to.

139
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,400
[GIO] Yes, this seems
to be the right place.

140
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:41,900
Wait.

141
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,367
Why?

142
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,600
Your shoelaces.

143
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:50,800
My shoelaces seem fine.

144
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:56,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:58,233
[LUNA] Gio, what are you doing?

146
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,100
I feel like someone's
following us.

147
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,267
Huh?

148
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,600
Just relax.

149
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:15,867
I checked and there's nobody.

150
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:37,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:40,833
[PHONE RINGING]

152
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:42,633
Hello, boss?

153
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:47,600
We're already tailing that Gio
and Luna here in Lawang Lupa.

154
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:51,400
[ANDY] Don't stop until you get
the clue for the treasure.

155
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,267
- Yes, boss.
- [PHONE BEEPS]

156
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,533
Hear that?

157
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,967
[CHESKA] Geez!

158
00:10:11,967 --> 00:10:14,200
I'm so bored!

159
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,567
If we're not going
to look for evidence

160
00:10:16,567 --> 00:10:20,333
and I won't get
any material for my podcast,

161
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:22,133
I need something to do.

162
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,633
Something to keep me occupied.

163
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:25,467
You'll find something to do.

164
00:10:25,467 --> 00:10:27,600
Wait, what's Raphie
doing over there?

165
00:10:28,533 --> 00:10:29,933
Let's go check.

166
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:32,933
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- He's locked in.

167
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,700
Hey!

168
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:37,767
- Let me see.
- What's that?

169
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:39,033
- Wow!
- Give it back!

170
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:41,033
- Are those fashion sketches?
- Those are nice!

171
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:43,267
- They're beautiful!
- Don't look at them.

172
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:44,667
- So secretive.
- We were just curious.

173
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:47,133
Why won't you show us?
They're great.

174
00:10:47,133 --> 00:10:50,433
You're just making fun of me.

175
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:52,000
[CHESKA] What?

176
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,167
Come on, Raphie.

177
00:10:54,167 --> 00:10:58,033
Don't you believe Trixie?

178
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:01,133
Look at her.
She has great style.

179
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:03,367
- A fashionista!
- She's right.

180
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:05,300
Actually, my brother
Martin has an ex-girlfriend

181
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,267
who is a fashion designer,

182
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:09,300
so I know a good design
when I see one.

183
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:11,133
[CHESKA] You know, Raphie...

184
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,500
you've got talent.

185
00:11:13,267 --> 00:11:17,700
You should pursue that
instead of working here.

186
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:21,167
Well, that's the dream.

187
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:25,467
If there were a fashion design
school on the island,

188
00:11:25,467 --> 00:11:27,767
I would've enrolled myself.

189
00:11:27,767 --> 00:11:30,800
Then go to Manila
and study there.

190
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,333
Oh, I can't do that.

191
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:36,667
Why not? Is it a money issue?

192
00:11:36,667 --> 00:11:38,400
If you want, Raphie,

193
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:41,767
I can help you find
a part-time job

194
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,333
while you're studying.

195
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:45,800
You can also stay with me
to save money on rent.

196
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,667
Would that work for you?

197
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:49,233
Really, Miss Trixie?

198
00:11:49,233 --> 00:11:50,133
Absolutely!

199
00:11:50,133 --> 00:11:52,067
[CHESKA] See, Raphie?

200
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:53,800
You can make your dream
a reality.

201
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,567
Go for it.

202
00:11:55,567 --> 00:12:01,233
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:04,100
Thank you, Miss Trixie,
but I can't accept your offer.

204
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:06,667
I can't leave
my sister here.

205
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:08,833
[CHESKA] Oh, right.

206
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:11,533
Of course you can't.

207
00:12:11,533 --> 00:12:13,067
[TRIXIE] Alright, Raphie.

208
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:14,767
If you ever change your mind,

209
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,433
just let me know, okay?

210
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,867
Can I look at your sketches?

211
00:12:19,867 --> 00:12:21,700
- Please.
- Don't judge it, okay?

212
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,833
- Let's have a look.
- Let me see.

213
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:26,133
This is my first sketch.

214
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:28,100
Oh my god, Raphie!
It's beautiful!

215
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,700
- It is!
- Wow!

216
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:31,867
[RAPHIE] This would
look good on you, Miss Trixie.

217
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:33,267
This one.

218
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,300
Are we going
the right way, Sari?

219
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,300
Yes, sir. Straight ahead.

220
00:12:42,633 --> 00:12:43,800
Wait.

221
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:45,767
Maybe we should
take a break first?

222
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:47,467
Alright, let's stop here.

223
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:24,600
Sir?

224
00:13:25,767 --> 00:13:27,367
Can I ask you a question?

225
00:13:28,267 --> 00:13:29,233
What is it?

226
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:31,500
How are you?

227
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:39,333
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:41,733
There's a lot going on
at the hotel.

229
00:13:43,633 --> 00:13:45,467
And Sir Leon,

230
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:46,900
your best friend,

231
00:13:47,733 --> 00:13:49,333
is in jail.

232
00:13:51,267 --> 00:13:57,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:13:57,733 --> 00:14:00,333
I don't know how
to answer your question.

234
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:03,433
Why?

235
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:08,367
No one has ever asked me
that before.

236
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:15,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:17,433
I feel bad for Leon.

238
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:19,200
He's my buddy.

239
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:22,333
We've been best friends
since we were kids.

240
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,567
I just... [SIGHS]

241
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:28,700
I just didn't expect our lives
would turn out this way.

242
00:14:30,533 --> 00:14:32,333
What do you mean?

243
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:34,633
When my father died
and left us the hotel,

244
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:38,233
all I wanted
was to get it running.

245
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:40,433
And look at me now.

246
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:44,400
I'm looking for clues to
get my friend out of jail

247
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:47,633
and uncover the truth
behind our fathers' deaths.

248
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:55,867
You'd do anything
for your family.

249
00:14:55,867 --> 00:15:02,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

250
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,400
So...

251
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,900
Are you guys good?

252
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:14,300
Let's get going.

253
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:21,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

254
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,467
Is it this way, Sari?

255
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,333
Yes. Straight ahead, sir.

256
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:42,933
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:48,267
[CELLPHONE BUZZING]

258
00:15:48,867 --> 00:15:49,967
Syvera here.

259
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:55,000
[MAN]<i> Syvera,
</i>the DNA test results are ready.

260
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,767
The blood I found?

261
00:15:56,767 --> 00:15:58,500
[MAN] Yes.

262
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,467
<i> It's a match.</i>

263
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:02,633
<i> The blood belongs to
Juan Soliman.</i>

264
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:06,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,667
Alright, I'll call you back.
Thank you.

266
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:10,733
Almazan's trial
is about to start.

267
00:16:10,733 --> 00:16:12,433
He's being transferred
to city jail.

268
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,533
[HENRI] Really?

269
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:16,300
Okay.

270
00:16:16,967 --> 00:16:19,300
We'll process his transfer.

271
00:16:20,967 --> 00:16:21,933
Alright.

272
00:16:21,933 --> 00:16:28,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:43,567
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

274
00:16:57,967 --> 00:17:01,700
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

275
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,367
He'll be transferred
to the city jail.

276
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:05,433
Perfect timing.

277
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:09,833
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,033
Time to teach him a lesson.

279
00:17:11,967 --> 00:17:14,600
I'll tell my friend,
the warden,

280
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:16,367
to make sure
he can't speak afterward.

281
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

282
00:17:18,733 --> 00:17:19,833
They'll take care of it.

283
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:23,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

284
00:17:23,633 --> 00:17:24,500
Okay.

285
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,600
I'll work on it.

286
00:17:28,167 --> 00:17:29,133
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

287
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:34,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,100
Kiko.

289
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,700
- Hmm?
- Kiko, where are we?

290
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:44,367
Just look around you.

291
00:17:44,367 --> 00:17:46,633
Look for what will match
the one from the book.

292
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:53,500
What if it's not here?

293
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:55,533
Papa said that the treasure
is located

294
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,167
inside the property
of Hotel 88.

295
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:58,833
So, you can look for it here.

296
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:05,733
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:18:16,133 --> 00:18:17,233
Wait...

298
00:18:17,233 --> 00:18:20,100
Let's read it again
instead of going in circles.

299
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,433
"Standing on five...

300
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,367
[JADE] But can't walk.

301
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:42,300
Follow the path
that never makes a sound.

302
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:46,733
The secret does not live
on paper,

303
00:18:46,733 --> 00:18:50,467
but at the back molded by time.

304
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:55,600
Read the line like a vow.

305
00:18:56,867 --> 00:18:59,100
Because that's
where it breathes...

306
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:01,400
the Oscalara."

307
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:07,700
On five...

308
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:14,200
[KIKO] Standing...

309
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,800
What can stand
but can't walk?

310
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,800
It's not a person,
because people can walk.

311
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:25,233
It could be a building.

312
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:27,400
It could also be a house.

313
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:29,867
That's possible.

314
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:33,300
Or could it be a tree,

315
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:34,667
or a pole.

316
00:19:36,667 --> 00:19:39,267
The secret does not live
on paper.

317
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:43,867
Where can you put secrets
aside from paper?

318
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:48,800
It can be written on,
but not paper.

319
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:51,233
Ground?

320
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,167
Is it the ground?

321
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,233
Let me read it.

322
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:06,200
[EDWARD] "Read the line...

323
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,833
like a vow.

324
00:20:11,433 --> 00:20:13,433
Because that's
where it breathes...

325
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:15,667
the Oscalara."

326
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,933
Oscalara?

327
00:20:20,567 --> 00:20:21,967
Isn't that like a house?

328
00:20:21,967 --> 00:20:23,533
A name?

329
00:20:23,733 --> 00:20:26,233
If we knew, we wouldn't
be here looking for it, right?

330
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:28,267
- Kiko.
- I'm just saying.

331
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:36,500
Wait, if...

332
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,800
If the letter O
was capitalized,

333
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:41,300
it means it can be
a person's name.

334
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:43,600
Or maybe it's a place or...

335
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,433
an object, right?

336
00:20:50,533 --> 00:20:51,767
Wait.

337
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,467
I think I've heard
the word "Oscalara" before.

338
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,567
I just can't remember
where I saw

339
00:20:58,300 --> 00:20:59,567
or heard it.

340
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:02,867
You've seen it here?

341
00:21:02,867 --> 00:21:06,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

342
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,633
[LUNA] Did we get it
wrong again?

343
00:21:13,433 --> 00:21:15,467
[GIO] That's impossible.
It can't be wrong.

344
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:19,400
If it's not at the top,
it might be at the bottom.

345
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:21,000
We'll have to dig.

346
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:24,833
If it was buried,
there should be a sign.

347
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:31,967
It says here that it's
located in the northwest.

348
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:36,433
Do you see that?

349
00:21:38,467 --> 00:21:39,567
Let's go.

350
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:46,500
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:21:51,033 --> 00:21:52,467
Do you see that?

352
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:54,633
[LUNA] Is that a rock?

353
00:21:57,567 --> 00:21:59,267
[GIO] Doesn't it look
like a tombstone?

354
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:02,733
It also matches
with the direction.

355
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:06,300
Northwest.

356
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:13,267
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

357
00:22:27,067 --> 00:22:28,767
Looks like they've found it.

358
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:31,633
[GUN COCKS]

359
00:22:31,633 --> 00:22:38,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

360
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:56,167
There really is
someone buried here.

361
00:22:57,700 --> 00:23:00,167
- Let's start digging.
- What?

362
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,067
We might find
the treasure there.

363
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,633
With the corpse?

364
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:07,867
Luna, if you don't want to,
I can do it myself.

365
00:23:08,533 --> 00:23:15,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

366
00:23:23,733 --> 00:23:24,967
[GRUNTS]

367
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:28,100
[GRUNTS]

368
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:33,667
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [SCREAMS]

369
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:36,700
Thieves!

370
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:39,300
Luna! Hurry up!

371
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:42,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

372
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:43,700
Hurry up!

373
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:49,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,433
This way.

375
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,400
Dad and I have been here
before.

376
00:23:52,533 --> 00:23:59,367
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

377
00:24:01,367 --> 00:24:04,833
"Five of them are standing,
but they don't walk."

378
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:11,000
We have followed the five
palm trees earlier.

379
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:18,300
The unwavering path refers to
the river we crossed earlier.

380
00:24:20,467 --> 00:24:22,133
This is the path's end.

381
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:26,700
[KIKO] It's a church.

382
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:30,200
What could be in here?

383
00:24:33,467 --> 00:24:34,767
Let's search the area.

384
00:24:35,700 --> 00:24:37,767
I'm sure we'll find
something here.

385
00:24:42,667 --> 00:24:43,633
Okay.

386
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:50,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

387
00:24:56,833 --> 00:24:57,933
[GIO] Luna, run faster!

388
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:00,333
- [LUNA PANTS]
- Hurry!

389
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,400
[LUNA GASPS, SCREAMS]

390
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:06,067
Luna!

391
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:08,200
[LUNA] Let go of me!
Let me go!

392
00:25:08,333 --> 00:25:09,467
Let me go! Gio!

393
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:10,700
[GIO] Luna!

394
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:11,733
[LUNA] Gio!

395
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:14,033
Let me go! Let me go!

396
00:25:14,167 --> 00:25:15,433
Luna!

397
00:25:15,567 --> 00:25:16,633
[GIO GASPS]

398
00:25:16,767 --> 00:25:18,000
What's this?!

399
00:25:18,133 --> 00:25:19,533
- Gio!
- What is this?!

400
00:25:19,667 --> 00:25:20,500
- Luna!
- Gio!

401
00:25:20,633 --> 00:25:21,967
Let go of me!

402
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:23,967
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [BODY THUDS]

403
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:26,033
[GIO] Luna! What is this?!

404
00:25:26,167 --> 00:25:26,967
Luna!

405
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:28,967
Let her go! Take me instead!

406
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:30,433
- Take me, not her!
- [THUDS]

407
00:25:30,567 --> 00:25:31,500
[BODY THUDS]

408
00:25:31,633 --> 00:25:37,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

409
00:25:39,133 --> 00:25:40,200
<i> Aah!</i>

410
00:25:41,667 --> 00:25:42,633
<i>- Sari!
- Hey!</i>

411
00:25:42,767 --> 00:25:44,033
[BODY THUDS]

412
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:49,067
<i>- What's that?
- Sari, what are you--</i>

413
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:51,933
<i>I'm just turning my
blouse inside out because--</i>

414
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:53,267
<i> Because we're lost?</i>

415
00:25:54,433 --> 00:25:55,700
<i> Kiko, Edward!</i>

416
00:25:55,833 --> 00:25:57,033
<i> Jade!</i>

417
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:59,033
<i>- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?</i>

418
00:25:59,167 --> 00:26:00,800
<i> Jade, you found it!</i>

419
00:26:01,467 --> 00:26:02,733
<i> Hey!</i>

420
00:26:02,867 --> 00:26:04,133
<i>- Kiko! Kiko!
- What are you doing, huh?</i>

421
00:26:04,267 --> 00:26:05,867
<i>And you said you could
be trusted!</i>

422
00:26:06,667 --> 00:26:07,833
<i> Gio.</i>

423
00:26:09,633 --> 00:26:10,533
<i> Luna?</i>

424
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:12,367
[GASPING]

425
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:15,100
<i>Martin told me to hug you
for him.</i>

426
00:26:15,233 --> 00:26:17,233
<i>We're carrying out
the plan.</i>

427
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:20,000
<i>- Nobody move!
- Put that down!</i>

428
00:26:20,133 --> 00:26:21,533
<i>Open the door
or I'll kill him!</i>

429
00:26:21,667 --> 00:26:22,833
<i> Put that down now!</i>
